concept.explain:
The grid-column property places an item between column grid lines.

Example:
grid-column: 2 / 3;

This shorthand is equivalent to:
grid-column-start: 2;
grid-column-end: 3;

This moves the item from column line 3 to column line 4.

The grid-row property places an item between row grid lines.

Example:
grid-row: 3 / 6;

This shorthand is equivalent to:
grid-row-start: 3;
grid-row-end: 6;

This moves the item from row line 3 to row line 6.
